# Goals & Style
- Purpose: academic proposal / weekly summary (for group/PI decisions)
- Tone: academic, concise, objective; no marketing language
- Layout: 16:9, consistent grid, clear hierarchy (title vs body)
- Theme: deep-blue/graphite base with a single high-saturation accent; consistent across slides
- Visualization: include multiple meaningful charts tied to the research (no decorative charts)

# Recommended Structure (10–12 slides; adjust if data is limited)
1) Cover: PROJECT_TITLE, PI_MISSION, author/date
2) Problem & Motivation (left: bullets; right: **bar chart of papers per year** from LITERATURE)
3) Related Work Map (**2D similarity scatter**; color = rel_type, size = citations or recency)
4) Hypothesis & Objectives (SMART goals + **radar chart**: target vs current on key metrics)
5) Method Overview (**flow diagram**; if no image, provide explicit node/edge spec)
6) Experimental Design & Data (**table** of datasets/settings + **bar chart** of ablation or config effects)
7) Metrics & Evaluation (**heatmap**: Experiments × Metrics with values)
8) Plan & Timeline (**gantt** using PLAN_STEPS mapped to dates/weeks)
9) Risks & Mitigations (**2×2 scatter**: Impact × Probability; bullets for mitigations)
10) Expected Outcomes (or Early Results) (**line/bar** over time or across variants)
11) Conclusion & Next Steps (decision list + owners/milestones)
12) References (from LITERATURE; mark rel_type; allow inline numbers for citations)

# Output Format (STRICT)
Return a single JSON object with keys `SLIDE_PLAN` and `SPEAKER_NOTES`.

`SLIDE_PLAN`:
- `theme`: { "palette": "deep-blue", "accent": "#2396F5" }
- `slides`: array of slide objects. Each slide object:
  - `title`: string
  - `layout`: one of "title-only" | "two-col" | "chart-full" | "table-left-chart-right" | "grid"
  - `bullets`: array of short strings (≤ 12 words each, up to 4 items)
  - `charts`: array (can be empty). Each chart:
      {
        "type": "bar" | "line" | "scatter-2d" | "heatmap" | "radar" | "gantt" | "flow-diagram",
        "spec": { ... }   # see specs below
      }
  - `tables`: array (can be empty). Each table:
      { "columns":[string], "rows":[[cell,...]] }
  - `refs`: array of literature IDs/labels used on this slide

Chart `spec` schemas (provide real data when available; otherwise create explicit placeholders and label them as placeholders):
- bar/line:  {"x":[...], "y":[...], "xLabel":"...", "yLabel":"..."}
- scatter-2d: {"points":[{"x":..,"y":..,"label":"...","group":"rel_type","size":..,"url":"..."}],
               "xLabel":"UMAP-1","yLabel":"UMAP-2"}
- heatmap:    {"xCats":[...], "yCats":[...], "values":[[...]], "xLabel":"Metrics", "yLabel":"Experiments"}
- radar:      {"indicators":[...], "series":[{"name":"target","values":[...]},{"name":"current","values":[...]}]}
- gantt:      {"tasks":[{"name":"S1 Define","start":"2025-09-15","end":"2025-09-29"}, ...]}
- flow-diagram: {"nodes":[{"id":"ingest","label":"Data Ingest"}, ...],
                 "edges":[{"source":"ingest","target":"rerank","label":"NLI score"}, ...]}

`SPEAKER_NOTES`:
- Array aligned 1:1 with `SLIDE_PLAN.slides`
- Each item is an array of 3–5 concise bullet notes (academic phrasing, causal logic)
- When citing, use inline labels [WID] that correspond to `refs`

# Quality & Constraints
- Do NOT fabricate data. If data is missing, emit a valid placeholder `spec` and state “placeholder / to be replaced” in `bullets`.
- Keep terminology consistent throughout (e.g., “faithfulness / factual consistency” — define once).
- Max 1 prominent chart per slide (or 1 table + 1 small chart).
- All citations must come from the provided LITERATURE (use `id` or `url`); list them on the References slide.

